CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F433A1769004141
OL,3,CPoliceman in tears as he is cleared of
OL,4,Ckilling motorist in high-speed pursuit
OL,6,F"At the conclusion of that process, I
OL,7,Fcame to the decision, which is my
OL,8,Fdecision as the judge of the law, that
OL,9,Flooking at this as a whole, the
OL,10,Fevidence in this case is not
OL,11,Fsufficient to allow any jury to find
OL,12,Fthat the defendant Matthew Pike drove
OL,13,Fdangerously or drove carelessly.
OL,15,F"This is because prosecution expert
OL,16,Fwitness told you that in his opinion,
OL,17,Fas an expert in police pursuits,
OL,18,Ftraining and driving, Matthew Pike did
OL,19,Fnot drive dangerously and did not
OL,20,Fdrive carelessly at any stage during
OL,21,Fthe pursuit of the VW Tiguan.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
